1
00:00:00,590 --> 00:00:05,440
Now, what's the effect of these two home environments on John and Milton?

2
00:00:05,710 --> 00:00:10,400
Over a period of a week or two, there probably is no perceptible effect,

3
00:00:10,510 --> 00:00:14,960
but over a period of months and years, the effect is tremendous.

4
00:00:15,630 --> 00:00:21,519
John's environmental pattern leaves him refreshed, gives him ideas, tunes up his thinking.

5
00:00:21,630 --> 00:00:24,480
He's like an athlete being fed steak.

6
00:00:24,830 --> 00:00:29,200
Milton's environmental pattern leaves him psychologically starved.

7
00:00:29,310 --> 00:00:31,680
His thinking mechanism is impaired.

8
00:00:31,789 --> 00:00:35,200
He's like an athlete being fed candy and beer.

9
00:00:36,190 --> 00:00:43,920
John and Milton may be on the same level today, but there will gradually be a wide gap between them in the months ahead,

10
00:00:43,950 --> 00:00:46,400
with John in the lead position.

11
00:00:47,150 --> 00:00:52,799
Casual observers will say, well, I guess John has more on the ball than Milton.

12
00:00:53,150 --> 00:01:03,200
But those of us who know will explain that much of the difference in job performance is the result of the difference in the mind food consumed by the two fellows.

13
00:01:03,789 --> 00:01:09,120
Every farmer in the Corn Belt knows that if he puts plenty of fertilizer with his corn,

14
00:01:09,150 --> 00:01:11,279
he's going to get a bigger yield.

15
00:01:11,630 --> 00:01:17,360
Thinking, too, must be given additional nourishment if we want to get better results.

16
00:01:18,029 --> 00:01:27,120
My wife and I, along with five other couples, spent a wonderful evening last month as guests of a department store executive and his wife.

17
00:01:27,550 --> 00:01:33,039
My wife and I lingered just a little longer than the others, so I had a chance to ask our host,

18
00:01:33,070 --> 00:01:36,960
whom I know well, a question that had been in my mind all evening.

19
00:01:37,230 --> 00:01:42,319
This was really a wonderful evening, I said, but I'm puzzled about one thing.

20
00:01:42,670 --> 00:01:50,160
I'd expected to meet mainly other retailing executives here tonight, but your guests all represented different fields.

21
00:01:50,269 --> 00:01:57,039
There was a writer, a doctor, an engineer, an accountant, and a teacher." He smiled and said,

22
00:01:57,039 --> 00:02:06,400
"'Well, we often do entertain retailing people, but Helen and I find it's very refreshing to mix with people who do something else for a living.

23
00:02:06,750 --> 00:02:13,120
I'm afraid if we can find our entertaining to people who have only interests similar to our own,

24
00:02:13,230 --> 00:02:16,240
we'd find ourselves in the old well-known rut.

25
00:02:16,510 --> 00:02:20,160
Besides, he went on, people are my business.

26
00:02:20,430 --> 00:02:26,160
Every day thousands of people of every occupational group imaginable visit our store.
